Detailed Description

The SIM Toolkit handler SimTkHandler holds the functionality for receiving SIM Toolkit events coming up from the protocolstack and provides an interface for the application to react to these events. If the underlying stack supports Simtk transaction ids, the methods with the SimTkTransactionId must be called.

CallApiRc SimTkHandler::AcceptCallSetup (  const ProactiveCause &  cause,
BOOLEAN  ctm = FALSE
)  const
 

The method AcceptCall(const ProactiveCause &) can be executed when SIM Toolkit is waiting for an answer to a previous sent message SimTkCallSetupMsg. With this function the application can accept the call setup request. If the method is executed, while SIM Toolkit is not waiting for a response, it has no effects, that means it will not lead to a call setup!

Parameters:
cause indicates, if the request was successful processed by the application or not.
ctm,TRUE if CTM/TTY is used
Returns:
TRUE, if the call accept was successfully initiated.

The method Inkey(const ProactiveCause &, const WString &) is the response for the SIM Toolkit request SimGetInkeyMsg.

BOOLEAN SimTkHandler::RejectCallSetup (  const ProactiveCause &  cause = UserDidNotAcceptCallSetupRequest  )  const
 

The method RejectCall() can be executed when SIM Toolkit is waiting for an answer to a previous sent message SimTkCallSetupMsg. With this method the application can reject the call setup request. If the method is executed, while SIM Toolkit is not wating for a response, it has no effects, that means it will not lead to a reject of an existing call! If the user is terminating the sim toolkit session he should give the proactivecause "TerminateByUser" to the method.

Returns:
TRUE, if the call reject was successfully initiated.

BOOLEAN SimTkHandler::SendIdleScreenAvailEvent (   ) 
 

The method SendIdleScreenAvailEvent sends the idle screen event to the simtoolkit dependend of retrieved event list.

BOOLEAN SimTkHandler::SendLanguageSelectEvent (   ) 
 

The method SendLanguageSelectEvent sends the selected language event to the simtoolkit dependend of retrieved event list. The language 'ExtLanguage' itself is retrieved by the ADC where it has to be set before. Reason for that is because the async language request sent by the simtoolkit reads out the value stored in ADC automatically.

BOOLEAN SimTkHandler::SendSimTkRefreshRsp (   ) 
 

The method SendSimTkRefreshRsp sends the SimTkRefreshRspArg back to the stack. The transaction id and cause are stored temporally in SimTkDispatcher. This shall be sent only in case FDN was refreshed.

BOOLEAN SimTkHandler::SendUserActivityEvent (   ) 
 

The method SendUserActivityEvent sends the user activity event to the simtoolkit dependend of retrieved event list.

BOOLEAN SimTkHandler::SetActiveExtLanguage (  const WString &  language  ) 
 

The method SetActiveExtLanguage stores the activated language selected by the MMI into ADC. SendLanguageSelectEvent reads out that value and send it back to the SimToolkit when necessary.

BOOLEAN SimTkHandler::SetSimRefreshPossible (  BOOLEAN  isrefreshable  ) 
 

The method SetSimRefreshPossible indicates that the Simtk is allowed or not allowed to refresh the sim.

BOOLEAN SimTkHandler::SetSimResetPossible (  BOOLEAN  isresetable  ) 
 

The method SetSimResetPossible indicates that the Simtk is allowed or not allowed to reset the sim. This is equivalent to a sim-detach / sim-attach procedure.

void SimTkHandler::UpdateSimTkProfileReq (  const SimTkProfile &  profile_data  )  const
 

The method UpdateSimTkProfileReq sends a request to the OM-process to change the current Terminal Profile. MMI then receives the messages SimTkProfileSetCnfMsg (on success) or SimTkProfileSetRejMsg (no success).
